  91 -def _dir_filter(self): 

  92      # Using introspection, mimic dir() by adding up all of the __dicts__ 
  93      # for the current class and all base classes (type(self).__mro__ returns 
  94      # all of the classes that make it up) 
  95      # Basically filters by: 
  96      # __x__ OK 
  97      # __x bad 
  98      # _classname bad 
  99      def check(s): 
 100          if s.startswith('__'): 
 101              if s.endswith('__'): 
 102                  return True 
 103              else: 
 104                  return False 
 105          else: 
 106              for typename in typenames: 
 107                  if typename in s: 
 108                      return False 
 109              return True 

 110       
 111      keys=sum([list(c.__dict__.keys()) for c in type(self).__mro__], []) 
 112      typenames=["_%s" % c.__name__ for c in type(self).__mro__] 
 113      ret=[s for s in list(set(keys)) if check(s)] 
 114      ret.sort() 
 115      return ret

7320  # Initialize the alternative namespace b2.*, and clean-up the 
7321  # dir listing of Box2D by removing *_swigregister. 
7322  # 
7323  # To see what this is, try import Box2D; print(dir(Box2D.b2)) 
7324  from sys import version_info 
7325  if version_info >= (2, 5): 
7326      from . import b2 
7327  else: 
7328      import b2 
7329  del locals()['version_info'] 
7330   
7331  s=None 
7332  to_remove=[] 
7333  for s in locals(): 
7334      if s.endswith('_swigregister'): 
7335          to_remove.append(s) 
7336      elif s!='b2' and s.startswith('b2'): 
7337          if s[2]=='_': # Covers b2_* 
7338              setattr(b2, s[3].lower() + s[4:], locals()[s]) 
7339          else: # The other b2* 
7340              if s[3].isupper(): 
7341                  setattr(b2, s[2:], locals()[s]) 
7342              else: 
7343                  setattr(b2, s[2].lower() + s[3:], locals()[s]) 
7344  for s in to_remove: 
7345      del locals()[s] 
7346   
7347  del locals()['s'] 
7348  del locals()['to_remove']
